  "Jonathan Nelson is CEO of Providence Equity Partners, the private equity firm he founded in 1989.",
  "Providence has invested in more than 160 companies, many in the media, communications, education and information industries.",
  "The firm sold PADI, the scuba diving certification company, for over $700 million in 2017, tripling its initial investment.",
  "Nelson studied economics at Brown; where he sits on the governing board, before getting an MBA at Harvard."
